The emergency declaration was his way to sidestep a recalcitrant Congress to advance a key policy priority.
“I went down there neutral on this question, didn’t know whether or not I’d support a national emergency,” Kinzinger said.
Hoyer said Tuesday that, even if Trump’s veto is sustained, it will mark a political victory for Democrats.